<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Llily Willowfyre</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=teapray>Teapray</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 206<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/20/03 7:09 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~abenlen/yawn.JPG height=100 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Disagreements</span><hr size=1> I think that as long as people come together in any forum or venue, there are going to be disagreements.  I don't think that that really reflects poorly on the people involved.  It's just the way people tend to be.<br>
<br>
    I had a disagreement with a chap a couple of months ago.  He called me a camp and kill stealer, shouted it out to the whole zone (which is sorta funny, since the zone empty but for us).  I believed myself to be in the right.  I was upset by the incident. <br>
<br>
    So, I came and posted about it here.  But... I was asking for other's points of view.  There were two of us, we both believed ourselves to be right... one of us was wrong in this situation.  And when I posted in soapbox, I accepted the possibility that I might have been the one who was in the wrong.  And even though the community sided with me, I did receive some tips on how I might have better handled myself to help defuse that sort of situation in the future.   And I am grateful for that.<br>
<br>
   But the lady who came here?  Ranted about a situation, then became defensive and abusive to others who posted that they did not agree with her position.  AFAIK, she maintained that she was 100% right in her view, and we were assholes for not supporting her.   She came across as being rigid, dogmatic, and combative.  She gave no signs of conceding that there might be another valid point of view.<br>
<br>
   I don't care if she lost a child.  I don't care if she is a thirteen year old who is gaming for the first time.  I don't care if she ever got raped, robbed, or assaulted.  I don't care if she had called in sick the day her office pooled on the lotto, and lost out on her share of 65 million dollars.  And from the way she was posting her, I sincerely doubt if she cared on whit if any of the above happened to the person that tried to RP with her, or any that have responded to her thread.  The only thing I care about is how she conducts herself in the EQ community that she and I are a part of.<br>
<br>
And she has behaved poorly. <p>-- <br>
